{
  "stem": "3012.4",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We didn't know what kind of treatment-- I mean, 'treatment' is always in quotation marks, when it comes to a concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I don't remember what they gave me, or how they treated me.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "All I remember that after a number of days, it was still dark outside.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I woke up.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I felt something very heavy pressing on my right shoulder.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I couldn't figure out, because there was no lamp, no light, no nothing in the block, in the area where I was.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But then gradually, as dawn was breaking, I realized that the middle-aged lady next to me died.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And probably, in her last moments of life, ended up on me.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So I tried to disengage myself as gently as I could.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It was a terrible experience.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "At the same moment, I saw Mother emerging from the door, near the door.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "I was on the upper level of a cot-- or bunk, or whatever you call it-- and Mother was approaching me and sort of trying to help me down.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And she said, my dear child, I'll take you back to the block, because Valerie-- she's Valerie Lovy, L-O-V-Y, she's living in Israel now-- told me that after a few days of-- she just found out, the friend, Valerie, from the same town where we came from-- that she just found out that the sick are being picked up after a few days at the revier, taken away, and then nobody ever heard anything about them or from them.",
      "word_count": 79
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I was terribly weak.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I don't know whether I mentioned it, I had some kind of dysentery.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "What was called in Auschwitz the Ukrainian.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I don't know why, maybe that's how they called it on the Russian front, I don't know.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "But it was just terrible.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
